figgy.title: Create static pages for service Privacy Policy and Terms of Service agreement

comments.body: Yes, I think we can just close this. There is a separate effort to post a takedown policy and form, and link to it from the viewer, so I think that will wind up addressing some of this anyway.

Update after discussion at checkin and follow-up with @kelea99

For bibdata items:
- We'll use the bibliographic fixed field type to map to the high-level type BNF wants. These should already be in the figgy records as "format" (not displayed for some reason) see the list at https://www.oclc.org/bibformats/en/fixedfield/type.html
- We'll also include the "type" field as a narrower term.

For pulfa items:
- We'll default to "text" for now.
- We discussed the best way to override this value and believe it should be done in finding aids as per the conclusions from the Archival Description in Figgy Working Group. Follow-up issue: #4009

Formats that may come from bibdata are here: https://github.com/pulibrary/marc_liberation/blob/94c77e2c582178c977ec7cafcf3a21aa42f52d8c/marc_to_solr/lib/format/bib_format.rb#L26-L34

2 others that may be in the catalog are coins, senior theses. these are visible as the "format" facet values (see front page of catalog)
